cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.DB, cs.MM

This paper discusses the compliance of research data services to the FAIR guiding principles, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The use case of retrieving spatially and temporally annotated images is discussed, which is relevant to sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), databases (cs.DB), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
